      "id": 11,
      "options": {
        "content": "## Honest gap list\n\nOTLP export today (`crates/pramen-core/src/observe.rs` → `export_metrics_otlp`) only pushes:\n\n| OTLP name | Kind |\n| --- | --- |\n| `pramen.rows_in` / `pramen.rows_out` | counter |\n| `pramen.batches_in` / `pramen.batches_out` | counter |\n| `pramen.bytes_in` / `pramen.bytes_out` | counter |\n| `pramen.run_duration` | gauge (seconds) |\n\nAttributed with `pipeline=<metadata.name>` and `service.name=pramen`.\n\n**Not emitted as metrics yet** (architecture §13). Use structured logs (`--log-format json`) and CLI inspectors until the registry grows:\n\n| §13 signal | Current operator surface |\n| --- | --- |\n| Channel occupancy / in-flight bytes | Runtime options only (`targetBatchBytes`, `maxInflightBytes`); no gauge |\n| Stage latencies (source/transform/sink) | Not histogrammed |\n| Retry counts and ages | Provider faults typed in logs; no counter |\n| Checkpoint age / completion | `pramen run` log lines (`checkpoint store consulted`, `checkpoint updated`); store files/rows |\n| Rejected records | `pramen ai status` / `ai review` (`rejected` count) |\n| WASM compile / invoke / trap / fuel / memory | Host traps in logs; no OTLP instruments |\n| AI queued / submitted / completed / reused / invalid / reviewed / failed | `pramen ai status` ledger counts |\n| Tokens / cost / provider latency / batch age | `ai evaluate` reports; ledger rows; not OTLP |\n| AI cache hit rate / model·schema cardinality | Ledger reuse on replay; no hit-rate metric |\n\nDo **not** invent PromQL for the missing rows — extend `RunMetrics` + `export_metrics_otlp` first, then add panels.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "Gaps vs architecture §13",
      "type": "text"
    }
